data.text:
Allison Musselman returned to Texas A&M in the summer of 2019 and serves as the Athletic Trainer for the SEC champion soccer team.

She spent the previous two seasons handling the prevention and care of injuries for Aggie softball's student-athletes.

Musselman spent 2018-19 as Athletic Trainer for the Auburn University soccer team before returning to Aggieland. She was a Graduate Assistant Athletic Trainer at A&M from 2016-18, when she worked primarily with Aggie tennis. She began her career as Athletic Trainer at Matrix Sports Care and Rehabilitation of Frisco in 2015-16.

She is certified by the National Athletic Trainersâ€™ Association, Texas Athletic Training Board, and is an approved CAATE Clinical Preceptor.

Musselman, a Dallas native, is a 2015 graduate of Oklahoma State University, where she earned her bachelor's degree in Athletic Training. She added her master's in Health Education at Texas A&M in 2018.
